    <h1 class="big-heading">Symptoms of Drug Abuse</h1>

    <p>

        Identifying signs of drug addiction and use can be challenging, but early recognition is crucial to prevent
        long-term harm. Some signs of drug addiction include regularly using the drug, intense cravings, increasing drug
        use over time, taking larger doses than intended, ensuring a steady supply, spending money despite financial
        difficulties, neglecting work or social responsibilities, continuing to use despite problems, engaging in risky
        behaviors, spending a significant amount of time on the drug, failing to stop despite attempts to quit, and
        experiencing withdrawal symptoms.

        <br><br>

        Signs of drug use in teenagers or family members may include frequent absences, physical health issues,
        neglecting appearance, being secretive, drastic behavior changes, and missing money or items from the home.

    </p>

