    <p>

        Signs and symptoms of drug use or intoxication vary depending on the drug. For example, marijuana can cause
        euphoria, increased heart rate, dry mouth, and decreased coordination, while K2 or bath salts can cause extreme
        anxiety or agitation, hallucinations, and violent behavior.

        <br><br>

        It's essential to seek professional help for drug addiction or use since substance use disorders can have severe
        consequences on a person's health and life. Some warning signs of addiction include continuing to use drugs
        despite negative consequences, strong cravings or urges, neglecting responsibilities or relationships,
        developing a tolerance, and experiencing withdrawal symptoms.

        <br><br>

        If you or someone you know is struggling with addiction or drug use, seeking help from a healthcare provider or
        mental health professional is crucial. Addiction is treatable, and there are many resources available to help
        overcome it.

    </p>

